supplemental awards are non-competing awards that increase the funding to an existing grant above and beyond what was originally awarded. reasons for supplemental awards:if you have found a supplemental opportunity or if a program officer has requested that you apply to one, please reach out to research development.nih offers three main types of supplemental funding:nsf offers many supplements designed to achieve specific objectives. below is a sample of supplemental funding opportunities at nsf. search for more opportunitieshere.other federal agencies do not typically have standing supplemental funding opportunities. they may however, occasionally issue one via grants.gov, a special notice, their program webpage or other mechanism. agencies known to do this are the department of defense, nasa, department of energy, u.s. department of agriculture, department of transportation and the department of education.